column1: CLONE - BPM: W6 RTX QA Testing of Purchase Request (PR) Hold PR Issue Resolution in Agile Point
column35:
Purchase Request (PR) Hold
 PR Issue Resolution

Due 10/3
column124:
Deliverables:
 # Test cases that were used for testing in the dev environment (provided by AgilePoint with the exception of GTAA and CORE OS)
 # A plan for key tasks presented in the leader’s intent (attached) ß do not overthink this; this is just between you and either me or Kathleen and can either be written or done as a meeting. As to how to plan to attend meetings – I know you plan to. Let’s mark that one complete.
 # Test results and any supporting documentation for audit purposes, including tester AND customer results. We’ve talked about being audited before. Same rules apply across projects.
 # A recommendation on the risk level prior to deploy (high, medium, low) with supporting argument presented to either myself or Kathleen first, then your team
 # A weekly email to me on how many hours you put towards AgilePoint (helps me report out accurately on both projects). You can start by responding to this with whatever you charged for last week, what work you are doing, and how it’s going. Again, don’t overthink. A few simple sentences is fine. “We’ve been testing in QA and working with the customer on UAT, working through some bugs, we plan to deploy on x date” is a better report than “I ran 8 tests and wrote 5 bugs”.
 # System of record will be JIRA. You will be responsible for adding user stories and tasks as appropriate on your team board (NOT the Synergy one). If you have questions on bugs, user stories, or tasks, please reach out. Kathleen and I are expecting questions. What exactly will these stories/tasks etc. look like? You will need to make a recommendation to your team on how to handle. This is more waterfall than agile. The rules I have learned for Leader’s Intent is that it should cover the who, what, where, and why, but not the HOW. That is up to you. You have the guidelines, you understand the audit process and know what information someone looking to do an audit would be looking for.

If you have questions on bugs, user stories, or tasks, please reach out. Kathleen and I are expecting questions. What exactly will these stories/tasks etc. look like? You will need to make a recommendation to your team on how to handle. This is more waterfall than agile. The rules I have learned for Leader’s Intent is that it should cover the who, what, where, and why, but not the HOW. That is up to you. You have the guidelines, you understand the audit process and know what information someone looking to do an audit would be looking for.

column1: NET - 001 - If Failover of Services do not work at a hub it risks cancellation of production events jeopardizing Q1 uplift schedule
column35:
2/21 - Current Dry Run plans for remaining sites are - Seattle Dry run on 3/4, Chicago Dry Run 2 on 3/16 

2/11 Dry Run at Chicago was conducted successfully. It served as a effective preparatory step in identifying potential failure points to be rectified for future transition and uplift at Chicago. Review of identified failure points and rectification plan for resolving those is ongoing.

2/7 Recently "Chicago CAB Dry Run representation" was postponed from first week of Feb because the captive portal for Guest Wireless currently only works when hosted out of Chicago. (The guest wireless is used not only for "actual guest connections" but also for other heritage orgs to VPN back to home networks). 

1/27 In general planned downtime on a hub for a production event (Dry Run OR Uplift event) occasionally results in a discovery of a service that is not failing over correctly.
Depending of which service is not failing over correctly the production event may get canceled OR production event will not get approval till remediation is in place
This may jeopardize Q1 completion of hub uplifts.

column1: Novation delay slowing Equinix ticket creation for deployment related activities
column35:
Deployment activities for Uplift and Transition need tickets opened with Equinix vendor on Equinix portal. These tickets are about various activities - Hub site visit / Hub equipment shipment delivery and pickup / cage access to name a few. Overall in the past we have created around 20 odd tickets for an uplift event. 

At this time Equinix portal is down  for novation related activities. So team is unable to open any tickets for fast approaching uplift and transition deployment timeline. (Dallas Uplift is targeted between 1/19 - 1/21 going into weekend and Chicago transition and uplift is targeted between 2/9 - 2/14.

The Novation started on 12/20 and was expected to complete by 12/27. However Equinix is still working thru it with no ETA in site except "will take 7 to 10 days" from Monday (1/10). This has been escalated at Equinix.

Since Equinix portal is down only for RTX/Collins purposes - it is not down otherwise - Equinix has provided a work around of assigning the Equinix CSM as the "Ticket creator" for RTX. This person will create tickets based on excel sheets we sent under Equinix account to be reconciled later. This workaround is not ideal and would prefer to have the system available as planned.

This has been escalated at Equinix with Allison Wussler(Account Executive) and Elisabeth (CSM).

column1: NET - 001 - Novation completion may slow down uplift work next week
column35:
Novation completion delay at Equinix has rendered Equinix portal in accessible for project team (in fact ALL of RTX). _(See explanation of Novation and importance of Equinix portal  below)_

As a work around - Equinix has assigned their CSM who will open tickets for project team in the interim. However this process is likely to slow the work down especially if there are any emergency tickets expected. Plan is to create a list of all known expected tickets by Friday for the CSM to enter into the portal and post that bulk creation handle it by case by case basis.

 

+Novation Explanation+

Novation is about "switching company name from legacy names to RTX". Novation was expected to complete within 3-5 days - it was initiated around December 20 however due to some "script" resources needed at Equinix this has not completed yet.

+Equinix portal explanation+

Equinix portal is used to create smart hands tickets/visit to site tickets/access tickets to cages etc. There is no ETA from Equinix for when that will complete (it has been escalated via a weekly call on 1/10 after several touch points in the interim).

column1: EIM hUTC CW to Workday Integration
column35: Initiative to onboard all remaining Heritage United Technology Contingent Workers to into Workday and then integrate into EIM for birthright provisioning. Program will be managed in a multi-release structure following the governance structure of EIM RoW Phase 1. HR partners will need to onboard disparate systems and processes for managing CW's into Workday prior to EIM consumption. First priorities based on size and criticality by business, have been identified as Canada and Poland. remaining 52 countries will be broken out by BU's and prioritization along with complexity.

column1: NET - 004 - Circuit Ordering Pause - Cost Savings Analysis
column35:
The RFP was a point to point NETWORK and savings were presented to the business units based on this design. Cost savings need to be re-evaluated since the design has been changed from point to point to MPLS. The disparity observed for the cost savings documented on the original point to point design vs the MPLS design may necessitate another redesign for some sites so that synergies promised can be achieved.

 

1/5/22 - We met with the finance team to review the 1M credit that has been received and to determine how it will be allocated. This is still being worked out.  We are also doing a cost analysis of the savings vs current costs. Once the analysis is complete, we will review with the BUs so they know their costs. We are authorized to submit the rest of the remote site circuit orders for RIS, RMD, and PWC/A

 

1/10/22 - working to complete a cost savings analysis for PW to get sign off to be able to move forward with the rest of the remote site circuit orders. Need to confirm bandwidth on the sites and confirm that one specific site has one or two circuits, as we are seeing conflicting information on different spreadsheets. 

1/12/22 - RIS and RMD have been resubmitted to ATT. Finalizing the list for PW to submit

 

1/14/22 - Still trying to get confirmation from PW to place their remote site orders. Frank is working with PW today and Monday to get confirmation

1/21/22 - PWC/A orders have been submitted. All phase 1 remote site orders are now submitted, with exception to Puerto Rico, which was a no bid from ATT. Moving Puerto Rico to phase 2. The finance team is still working out the 1M credit allocation

If: The Service Desk support for ADX Migrations is not in place

Then: We will not be able to begin Beta or Production migrations

Else:  (NA)

column1: Additional Features for FOSS Enterprise Service
column35: Stakeholders have additional feature work they want completed as part of the FOSS ES development in 2022.  This work exceeds the available development resources, but is desired to be completed.  The time or money required would need to be found/asslocated.

The cost of running Open Shift ARO could be higher than the initial licensing costs associated with the Dissynergy for DevSecOps.  Sandbox investigation currently underway will be able to confirm the actual costs.

If the transition from Azure Dev Ops to another RTX approved pipeline is required then cost and schedule may be increased
 
Mitigation/next steps:
 * Partner with DevOps team to evaluate and build plan to migrate to standard platform

If architecture resource is not onboarded by mid-January, 2022 then the cost and schedule will be increased
 
Some architecture impacts: upgrade from sitecore 9 --> 10 and P5 (sandbox) to P3 (production) Azure cloud. 
 
Next steps: * Open internal req. - leveraging loan-in architects in interim
 * Normal HR onboarding processes need to be expedited

column1: RTXConnect - Pivot to DoZen subscription software vs in-house intranet development
column35:
Dependency on Partnerships, Cyber, Legal to assist in finalizing agreement and requisite reviews (3PLA, 3PRA, etc.)

*Owner:* RTXConnect

*Mitigation Plan:* 
 * Have decided on DoZen tool and moving forward.
 * The new business case forecast has been approved.
 * Dozen contract for the license and implementation services is in review and we do risk delays if we don't hurry and get contract signed so we can start implementation.
 * Hoping legal can finish approvals by 1/31
 * Legal will also be negotiating with ITWorx on the SOW cost for both 

 * Architecture role has been onboarded and we have started to involve them
 * As of 2/10, DoZen is still in contract negotiations, being reviewed by legal. DoZen implementation will be delayed.
 * Meeting on 2/10 between Teh's team and Vendor to understand next steps

*Target Date:* 1/31/22

column35: * Critical Dependency: Automation & Reporting Phase is dependent on rollout on XetaCloud (aka Aerocloud 2.0) in April 2022

DXC disentanglement: Ability to transition existing service from DXC to RTX in a seamless fashion

 

Mitigation:-

Managed through DXC for 2022

Desktop Procurement Strategy including staging/storage: Short Term: Leverage Future Tech as Enterprise VAR for imaging, tagging, overflow storage
Long Term:  Align to desktop strategy Warehouse strategy dependent on facilities collaboration (Drives staffing)

 

Adjust Future Tech contract to incorporate h-UTC
Partner with Facilities and the Business Units to right size hub strategy

column1: Alignment to ServiceNow platform timeline creates interim gap
column35:
Alignment to ServiceNow platform timeline creates interim gap for the management of Strategic Insourcing Ancillary system integration complexity stresses timeline and resources Ability to migrate all existing processes and capabilities from existing DTAMS (Eracent)

Mitigation:-

Create hybrid solution based on the guidelines above under DXC Disentanglement. Evaluate Axonious for system integration, cleanse, and normalization to run concurrently with “core greenfield” instance. 
Maintain existing Eracent platform mid-2023 to ensure full transition of edge services (Procurement Portal, Vulnerability Mgmt., etc)

column1: Hybrid solution constrains resources working out of multiple systems
column35:
Hybrid solution constrains resources working out of multiple systems
Foundational data accuracy issues
Disparate and multiple unmanaged sources of truth.

 

Mitigation-

Onboard core, strategic staffing, in the preparation phase (see timeline slide). Create formal Data Migration (accuracy) to Greenfield HAM/SAM Pro. Design integrated data/system architecture

column1: AMaaS efficiencies dependent on a new Corporate funding allocation model

Immediately prioritize accuracy and mgmt. of new procurements

column220:
23/Nov/21 3:15 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;PDC1 currently has 39 cameras and two NVR systems.  The existing surveillance system is end of life and reportedly not be monitored.

GSS team has agreed to monitor DC in the future.  Monitoring will occur at the Farmington Operations Center. 

GSS scheduled site survey with Convergint Technologies, preferred vendor.  Convergint provided the attached diagram depicting camera locations.  The diagram and quote contain 39 cameras and two NVR systems.

11/22/2021.  Meeting with Dan Doyle to transition the strategic partnership procurement process.  Didier and Ed are searching for an existing contract with Convergint.

Convergint will provide installation services for cameras and NVR systems.

11/29/2021.  Original design included POE switches that did not require additional power supply.  Confirm with Didier.

 ;;;

Targeting Dec 2021 for contract / quote completion, and Jan 2022 for installation.
